    "where c E [€/kWh] represents the electricity price for buying energy from the grid and depends on the implemented price schedule.",
    "The variables E CHILLER [kWh] and E PUMP [kWh] correspond to the energy consumption of the chiller and pumping system respectively, while E LOAD [kWh] represents the energy consumption of lighting services, appliances and building equipment.",
    "However, E LOAD is not included in R E for source agent since the energy required to satisfy the energy demand of lighting services and building equipment can be purchased only from the grid and the control action of the DRL agent can not influence their operation.",
    "The temperature-related term is determined by evaluating the presence of occupants and the indoor temperature conditions.",
    "When the building is not occupied, the temperature-related term is zero (i.e., R T = 0)."
